  "prompt": "What do we call video with words on it?",
  "response": "A video with words displayed on it can be referred to in several ways, depending on the context and purpose of the text. Some common terms include:\n\n1. **Subtitled Video**: If the words are intended to provide a translation or transcription of the spoken content, it is called a subtitled video.\n\n2. **Captioned Video**: Similar to subtitled videos, these have text that appears on the screen to convey dialogue, sound effects, or other audio elements, often for accessibility purposes.\n\n3. **Annotated Video**: If the text is used to add explanatory notes or commentary to the video content, it is an annotated video.\n\n4. **Text Overlay Video**: This term is often used when text is added for stylistic purposes, such as titles, headings, or other visual elements to highlight information.\n\n5. **Kinetic Typography Video**: When the words are animated to move in sync with audio or music, it is known as kinetic typography.\n\nLet me know if you need more specific information or examples!",
